  "text": "We considered a normalized optical density value <0.8 (which corresponds to a mean duration of infection of 155 days) according to the BED-CEIA incidence test as evidence of a recent HIV-1 infection. A recent study showed that the reliability of this test was high across duplicate specimens and different laboratories [CITATION_1] .",
